## Rules & Guidelines

### ✅ DO

- ✅ **Always import from `@/shared/utils/alert`**
- ✅ **Use `showAlert` for simple messages**
- ✅ **Use `showConfirm` for confirmations**
- ✅ **Test on web to verify alerts appear**
- ✅ **Provide clear, actionable error messages**

### ❌ DON'T

- ❌ **Never use `Alert.alert` directly**
- ❌ **Never use `window.alert` or `window.confirm` directly** (use utilities instead)
- ❌ **Don't assume alerts work on web without testing**
- ❌ **Don't use `Alert.alert` with complex button arrays on web** (they won't work as expected)

---

## Testing Checklist

Before marking a feature complete:

- [ ] All error messages use `showAlert` or `showConfirm`
- [ ] No `Alert.alert` calls remain in the codebase
- [ ] Alerts display correctly on web (test in browser)
- [ ] Alerts display correctly on native (test on device/emulator)
- [ ] Confirmation dialogs work on both platforms
- [ ] Error messages are clear and actionable

